A tragic construction accident occurred in Manhattan when a crane collapsed, killing at least four people and injuring many.
Residents had previously complained about unsafe working conditions and the rapid pace of construction.
The crane, part of a 43-story building project, fell onto nearby residential buildings, causing devastation.
Rescue efforts continued throughout the night to find survivors.
The incident raised concerns about crane safety in the city, highlighting the risks posed by these towering structures.
Investigations focused on the installation of a steel piece that led to the crane's catastrophic failure, emphasizing the need for stricter safety measures in construction projects.
